RAF WATCH

Interactive map of UK Royal Air Force activity using ADS-B data.

Hex codes are scraped from live-mobile-mode-s.eu. Flight traces
are fetched from globe.adsbexchange.com (tar1090 format) and
stored as binary containers, parsed client-side. The frontend is
static HTML/CSS/JS with MapLibre GL.

Setup

  uv run scripts/scrape_hex.py             Scrape hex codes
  uv run scripts/fetch_adsb.py             Fetch last 14 days of traces
  uv run scripts/fetch_adsb.py --days 7    Fetch last 7 days
  uv run scripts/fetch_bases.py            Fetch RAF base locations from OSM
  python -m http.server -d web             Serve and open localhost:8000

The fetch script caches results in data/cache/ and is resumable.
Each day's data is stored as a separate .bin file loaded on demand
by the date slider. Flight counts per day are included in the
manifest (data/manifest.json).

Binary format (per-day .bin files)

  [uint32 LE]  entry count
  per entry:
    [uint32 LE]  ICAO hex code as integer
    [uint32 LE]  byte length of JSON payload
    [N bytes]    raw JSON response from adsbexchange

Manifest format (data/manifest.json)

  {"2026-02-18": 138, "2026-02-19": 121, ...}

  Keys are dates with .bin files, values are flight counts.

Data sources

  Hex codes    https://live-mobile-mode-s.eu/overviewall.php?DGCountry=UK
  Traces       https://globe.adsbexchange.com/globe_history/
  Bases        OpenStreetMap via Overpass API (military=airfield)
